Unsolved Practical: Create an HTML document that includes a section with multiple card elements representing different articles. Use CSS to style these cards as follows:
•	Apply padding, margin, border, and border-radius to all card elements.
•	Ensure that the card elements have a fixed width of 300 pixels and are horizontally centered within the viewport.
.<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Article Cards</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <section class="card-container">
    <article class="card">
      <h2>Article 1</h2>
      <p>freedom</p>
      <button>read more</button>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h2>Article 2</h2>
      <p>republic day</p>
      <button> read more</button>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h2>Article 3</h2>
      <p>gandhi jayanthi</p>
      <button>read more</button>
    </article>
  </section>
</body>
</html>
card-container {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: center;
  }
  
  .card {
    width: 200px;
    margin: 20px;
    padding: 20px;
    border: 1px solid #3327a665;
    border-radius: 10px;
    box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(22, 82, 142, 0.811);
  }
  
  .card h2 {
    font-weight: bold;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  
  .card p {
    font-size: 16px;
    color: #b11818;
  }
